## Details about Problem

NuGet product used (NuGet.exe | VS UI | Package Manager Console | dotnet.exe):

NuGet version (x.x.x.xxx): 5.8

dotnet.exe --version (if appropriate): 

VS version (if appropriate): vs2019 Latest - MSBuild with /r restore option

OS version (i.e. win10 v1607 (14393.321)):

Worked before? If so, with which NuGet version: v5.7

## Detailed repro steps so we can see the same problem

1. When building a .net461 project from VS 2019 - performs a successful build and projects.assets.json file has all project references with dependencies listed.

 "XX.Credentials.Domain/1.0.0": {
        "type": "project",
        "dependencies": {
          "XX.Access.DataAccess": "1.0.0",
          "XX.Credentials.Formats": "1.0.0"
        },
        "compile": {
          "bin/placeholder/XX.Credentials.Domain.dll": {}
        },
        "runtime": {
          "bin/placeholder/XX.Credentials.Domain.dll": {}
        }
      },

2. When building the same project via Azure Pipelines -> nuget install (v5.8) -> nuget restore -> ms build (v16.8) -> the project.assets.json file misses the project dependencies , hence build failed with assembly missing issues.

 "XX.Credentials.Domain/1.0.0": {
        "type": "project",
        "compile": {
          "bin/placeholder/XX.Credentials.Domain.dll": {}
        },
        "runtime": {
          "bin/placeholder/XX.Credentials.Domain.dll": {}
        }
      },

